    p.
      The Buildbotics CNC controller accepts GCode from CAM software like
      Fusion 360, Mastercam, VCarve, BobCAD, MeshCAM, CamBam, and many others.
      Test your GCode for Buildbotics compatibility for free with
      #[a(href="https://camotics.org/") CAMotics].
    .clear

  section
    h2 Built-in Stepper Drivers
    .img-left
      img(src="images/steppers2.png", alt="Three different stepper motors")
    ul
      li 4 motor driver channels
      li Up to 6A per channel
      li 12v to 36v DC
      li Up to 256 microstepping
      li Smooth S-curve acceleration
      li Step rates up to 250k/sec per channel.

    p.
      Drive most NEMA 17, NEMA 23 and NEMA 34 motors. Preliminary support for
      4th axis as a rotary axis. The fourth driver can be synchronized to drive
      a single axis with two motors.  Here's a list of some
      #[a(href="/recommended-motors") motors we recommend].
    .clear

  section
    h2 Reliable Electronics
    .img-right: img(src="images/electrical_warning.png",
      alt="Electrical warning sign")
    p.
      We know you want your CNC to just work when you need it to.  Yet, many
      cheap CNC controllers were designed with little or no attention
      to electrical safety. The Buildbotics controller is protected from:

    ul
      li Over-current
      li Thermal overload
      li Under voltage
      li Reverse voltage
      li Short-circuit
      li Voltage spikes caused by motor stalls
    .clear

  section
    h2 Awesome Technical Support
    p.
      Get a hold of #[b a real person] when you need to. We provide technical
      support by #[a(href="mailto:info@buildbotics.com") email], phone or via
      #[a(href="//forum.buildbotics.com/") the Buildbotics forum].

    p.
      Check out #[a(href="store/#product-reviews", target="_blank") our reviews]
      to see just how much our customers love our technical support.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Stay Cool without a Fan
    .img-left: img(src="images/cool_without_fan.png",
      alt="A cool thermometer and a crossed out fan")

    p.
      The Buildbotics controller protects against thermal overload.
      Through careful selection of high-quality electronic components, the
      Buildbotics controller stays cool, without a fan, even while driving 6A
      motor loads. Going fan-less not only eliminates noise but also avoids
      sucking in dust and debris.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Dedicated Computer #[b not] Required
    .img-left: img(src="images/no_mach3_or_linuxcnc.png",
      alt="Mach3 and LinuxCNC both crossed out")

    p.
      A finely tuned PC running Mach or LinuxCNC is #[b not] needed.  You can
      access the Buildbotics controller's built-in software from any of your
      devices and be sure that your CNC will run smoothly and uninterrupted.

    p.
      You can even try out your GCodes online with our
      #[a(href="//demo.buildbotics.com/", target="_blank") free demo software].
    .clear

  section
    h2 Fast, Smooth & Accurate Stepping
    .img-left: img(src="images/stepdir.png", alt="Step and direction signals")

    p.
      Get maximum performance and accuracy from your CNC. The Buildbotics
      controller achieves smooth step rates up to #[i 250,000 per second]
      allowing you to use up to 256 microstepping at high speeds.
    .clear

  section
    h2 USB Gamepad Control
    img(src="images/buildbotics_gamepad_controls.png",
      alt="Buildbotics CNC Gamepad controller function diagram")
    p.
      Setup up cuts with ease and agility using the included gamepad.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Remote Monitoring with USB Camera
    .img-right
      img(src="images/logitech_C615-2.png", alt="USB camera")
    p.
      With the optional USB camera you can keep an eye on your CNC from
      anywhere using a Web browser or smartphone.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Wired or WiFi Networking
    p.
      The Buildbotics controller offers a modern Web interface accessible from
      a browser over your local network or WiFi.  A whole network of
      Buildbotics controllers can be managed from a single computer.
    img(src="images/buildbotics_network.png",
      alt="Many Buildbotics CNC devices connected by a network")
    .clear

  section
    h2 Free Simulation Software
    p.
      All the software you need to run GCode on your CNC machine is built
      in to the Buildbotics controller but you can also use our free
      simulation software to test your GCode before you run it.

    p.
      The #[a(href="//camotics.org/", target="_blank") CAMotics] CNC
      simulator computes 3D cut previews from GCode.  CAMotics can also send
      GCode directly to the Buildbotics controller over the network and track
      the machine position while it runs.

    a(href="//camotics.org", target="_blank")
      video(autoplay="", loop="", width="600")
        source(src="video/camotics.mp4", type="video/mp4")
    .clear

  section
    h2 RaspberryPi 3 Inside
    .img-right: img(src="images/raspberrypi3.png",
      alt="RaspberryPi CNC controller")
    p.
      The built-in Raspberry Pi 3 running Linux on a 16GiB microSD card
      provides massive potential for building your next big idea.  Install
      additional software or use Python to implement your own features.
    .clear

