  section
    h2 Tool Control
    img(src="images/spindles.png",
      alt="A DC CNC spindle next to a VFD CNC spindle")
    p.
      The PWM, enable and direction outputs can be used to control a wide
      array of tool heads. The RS485 connection drives high-speed VFD
      controlled air or water cooled spindles over two wires.
    .clear

  section
    a(name="breakout")
    .img-right: img(src="images/DB25_breakout_box.png", width="200",
      alt="Buildbotics DB25 I/O breakout box connection diagram")
    h2 I/O Breakout Box Included
    p.
      Limit switches, Z-axis probing, PWM spindle control, RS-485 spindle
      control, and e-stop switches can be easily connected via the included
      25-pin I/O breakout board using simple screw terminals.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Power Supply Options
    img(src="images/power_supplies.png",
      alt="Two types of MeanWell power supply")
    p.
      Connect any power supply which outputs 12-36v DC with at least 6A using
      the included power cable or buy the Mean Well GST280A-C6P power adapter
      on our store for a totally enclosed fan-less option.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Cables Included
    img(src="images/cables.png", alt="Included Buildbotics cables")
    p.
      The Buildbotics controller comes with time saving pre-made cables for
      connecting stepper motors, power supplies and load switches.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Built-in Load Switches
    .img-right: img(src="images/load_switch.png", width="400",
      alt="Buildbotics CNC controller controlling a compressor with an SSR")
    p.
      Two load switches, each capable of supplying up to 15A can power
      heated beds for 3D printers, extruders, vacuum tables or whatever else
      you can think of.

    p.
      For AC loads, an inexpensive
      #[a(href="//amazon.com/s/?field-keywords=solid+state+relay") SSR]
      switch can be used.  External relays can be used for higher amp
      DC loads.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Aluminum Enclosure
    img(src="images/enclosure.png",
      alt="Buildbotics CNC controller aluminum enclosure")
    .img-right: img(src="images/buildbotics_enclosure_base.png",
      alt="Diagram of Buildbotics CNC controller enclosure footprint")
    p.
      By carefully considering heat throughout the design process the
      Buildbotics controller dissipates heat through its fan-less aluminum
      enclosure without sucking in metal or wood shavings.

    p.
      Four screw holes allow the enclosure to be easily mounted on or near
      the machine.
    .clear

